{
  "texts": [
    "This variant is crucial for evaluating the role of in-context examples in guiding the student model to produce more accurate, relevant, and contextually appropriate rationales.",
    "• w/o LLaMA and w/o T5 exclude the rationale supervision provided by the respective teacher models during the distillation process.",
    "By removing the influence of either LLaMA or T5, these variants help us understand the individual contributions of each teacher's rationales.",
    "• w/o diverse teachers excludes the weaker teacher model, instead generating multiple rationales from the stronger teacher model.",
    "This variant is designed to test the effectiveness of using a diverse set of teachers, as opposed to relying on a single, potentially more robust teacher."
  ]
}